	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Five men are expected to appear in court after they were arrested for a drive-by shooting which left three people dead and two injured in Tsakane, east of Johannesburg on Friday. Police spokesperson Sergeant Lerato Mngomezulu said in a statement that the five men, aged between 20 and 34, were arrested on Tuesday. They will appear in the Tsakane Magistrate's Court. ALSO READ: Cop killed in Cape Town by gang of 6 It is alleged that the victims were sitting outside a house when an unknown vehicle stopped and its occupants started shooting. Five men were shot and two were declared dead by paramedics on the scene. ALSO READ: More questions than answers after Cape Town shooting leaves 3 children, man dead "Three victims were rushed to hospital and one among the three died at the hospital," Mngomezulu said. The motive for the shooting was not declared by the police. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  